WEBVTT

00:00:12.583 --> 00:00:15.208
"October 24, 2024"       "Floor 55: Grandzam"

00:00:15.208 --> 00:00:20.333
I understand the situation.
I'll explain it to the rest of the guild.

00:00:20.333 --> 00:00:25.083
There's that, and we're also requesting
temporary leave from the guild.

00:00:25.083 --> 00:00:26.833
Why is that?

00:00:26.833 --> 00:00:31.417
I'm starting to question the current
state of the Knights of the Blood Oath.

00:00:31.708 --> 00:00:33.042
Very well.

00:00:34.750 --> 00:00:36.125
However,

00:00:36.125 --> 00:00:39.458
you'll return to
the battlefield before long.

00:00:45.292 --> 00:00:50.792
"October 25, 2024"        "Floor 22"

00:00:53.375 --> 00:00:55.958
What an amazing view!

00:01:00.708 --> 00:01:04.750
Don't get too close
to the edge and fall.

00:01:09.958 --> 00:01:12.417
We bought a nice house.

00:01:12.417 --> 00:01:15.250
Although we're totally broke now.

00:01:16.542 --> 00:01:19.375
But we can live in peace here.

00:01:23.708 --> 00:01:24.875
Kirito?

00:01:25.333 --> 00:01:26.958
What's wrong?

00:01:26.958 --> 00:01:28.583
Hey, Asuna...

00:01:29.417 --> 00:01:33.375
Does our relationship
only exist in this world?

00:01:33.833 --> 00:01:38.833
You're making me angry, Kirito.
Even if this is a virtual world,

00:01:38.833 --> 00:01:41.167
my feelings are real.

00:01:43.917 --> 00:01:47.542
There's just one thing
I've learned here.

00:01:47.792 --> 00:01:51.000
To keep doing your best till the end.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:56.500
If we make it back to the real world,
I'll find you again, no matter what.

00:01:57.167 --> 00:01:59.958
And fall in love with you again.

00:02:16.417 --> 00:02:20.833
<i>The cowardly past that I'd acknowledged</i>

00:02:21.167 --> 00:02:26.667
<i>Still not understanding why,</i>

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:37.542
<i>I stand behind myself, scared</i>
<i>Projecting reality onto today</i>

00:02:37.917 --> 00:02:42.917
<i>I've drawn so many skies</i>

00:02:43.250 --> 00:02:47.625
<i>This must be my fleeting heart</i>

00:02:47.958 --> 00:02:50.333
<i>Out of control</i>

00:02:50.667 --> 00:02:55.917
<i>In my dreams, this body soars so high</i>

00:02:56.250 --> 00:03:01.083
<i>And it can brush away any fears that cling to me</i>

00:03:01.417 --> 00:03:07.583
<i>Asleep inside me, these budding</i>
<i>feelings start to expand</i>

00:03:07.917 --> 00:03:11.542
<i>I realize this, weak as I am...</i>
<i>As long as I had you</i>

00:03:11.875 --> 00:03:16.833
<i>I could stay strong in this dark world</i>

00:03:17.167 --> 00:03:22.833
<i>My heart will dream a long dream forever</i>

00:03:23.792 --> 00:03:26.250
<i>I want to always be with you</i>

00:03:26.583 --> 00:03:31.958
<i>I'll give you everything I have...</i>

00:03:35.042 --> 00:03:39.042
"The Girl of Morning Dew"

00:03:48.083 --> 00:03:50.833
<i>Normally, he's so brazen.</i>

00:03:50.833 --> 00:03:55.458
<i>But then he can be</i>
<i>surprisingly naïve or like a little kid</i>.

00:03:58.042 --> 00:04:01.042
<i>He's not younger than me, is he?</i>

00:04:06.042 --> 00:04:07.292
Kirito...

00:04:10.917 --> 00:04:14.542
I love you. Let's be
together forever, okay?

00:04:24.750 --> 00:04:26.917
Good morning, Kirito.

00:04:27.333 --> 00:04:28.625
Morning...

00:04:28.625 --> 00:04:31.708
D-Did you hear what I just said?

00:04:32.042 --> 00:04:34.375
Hear what?

00:04:34.667 --> 00:04:36.875
N-Nothing!

00:04:36.875 --> 00:04:40.292
Anyway, where should
we go play today?

00:04:41.625 --> 00:04:43.458
You know...

00:04:43.833 --> 00:04:48.208
We played yesterday and
the day before, for the whole day.

00:04:51.375 --> 00:04:55.292
So you don't want
to go out and have fun?

00:04:58.417 --> 00:05:02.208
Oh, I know a place
that could be fun.

00:05:07.417 --> 00:05:09.667
So where are we going?

00:05:09.667 --> 00:05:12.750
You'll find out when we get there.

00:05:14.917 --> 00:05:19.125
--Hey, carry me on your shoulders!
--C-Carry you?

00:05:19.125 --> 00:05:23.250
It's no fun always seeing
things from the same height.

00:05:23.542 --> 00:05:29.375
--It'll be easy with your STR parameter.
--W-Well, maybe, but...

00:05:32.458 --> 00:05:36.375
--Aren't you a little old for that?
--Age doesn't matter.

00:05:36.375 --> 00:05:39.250
Come on, no one's watching.

00:05:39.250 --> 00:05:41.792
O-Oh, fine...

00:05:45.667 --> 00:05:50.833
--If you turn around, I'll slap you!
--Isn't that kind of unreasonable?

00:05:54.375 --> 00:05:55.542
Ready.

00:06:03.792 --> 00:06:06.958
I can already see
the lake from here.

00:06:06.958 --> 00:06:08.583
I can't...

00:06:08.583 --> 00:06:11.500
Then I'll carry you later.

00:06:12.583 --> 00:06:16.417
Now let's go!
Set our course, north-northeast!

00:06:16.417 --> 00:06:17.583
Right.

00:06:31.333 --> 00:06:33.208
That scared me.

00:06:34.958 --> 00:06:37.792
It's not as if nobody's watching...

00:06:37.792 --> 00:06:40.417
I guess there are people around.

00:06:43.000 --> 00:06:47.417
--Go on. Wave back, Kirito.
--Not doing it.

00:06:48.125 --> 00:06:50.333
Should I get down?

00:06:51.083 --> 00:06:52.917
Hang on tight!

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:06.208
I heard a rumor
in the village yesterday.

00:07:06.208 --> 00:07:10.417
Here, deep in the forest,
they're known to appear.

00:07:11.625 --> 00:07:13.042
What are?

00:07:13.708 --> 00:07:14.833
Ghosts.

00:07:14.833 --> 00:07:19.292
D-Do you mean astral-type monsters?

00:07:19.708 --> 00:07:22.458
No, no. Real ghosts.

00:07:24.333 --> 00:07:27.625
They say the hatred
of monsters hunted here

00:07:27.625 --> 00:07:31.000
takes form and
wanders the field nightly.

00:07:35.792 --> 00:07:38.125
And we're nearly there...

00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:41.083
The place mentioned in the rumors?

00:07:41.083 --> 00:07:46.750
About a week ago,
a woodcrafter came to find wood.

00:07:47.583 --> 00:07:50.917
As he focused on
gathering it, night fell.

00:07:50.917 --> 00:07:56.125
And he caught a glimpse of
something white beneath a nearby tree.

00:08:04.125 --> 00:08:06.583
A monster or something else?

00:08:06.583 --> 00:08:10.875
The white shadow walked
slowly into a nearby grove of trees.

00:08:10.875 --> 00:08:12.917
H-H-H-Hey!

00:08:17.125 --> 00:08:19.500
L-L-Let me down!

00:08:20.583 --> 00:08:22.125
What's wrong?

00:08:30.292 --> 00:08:32.542
K-Kirito, over there.

00:08:32.542 --> 00:08:34.167
What is it?

00:08:39.792 --> 00:08:41.667
You gotta be kidding...

00:08:53.625 --> 00:08:54.875
That's...

00:08:55.750 --> 00:08:57.250
That's no ghost!

00:08:57.250 --> 00:08:59.417
W-Wait, Kirito!

00:08:59.917 --> 00:09:01.083
Jeez...

00:09:07.458 --> 00:09:09.542
Sh-She's a player?

00:09:11.333 --> 00:09:13.833
This is pretty strange.

00:09:13.833 --> 00:09:15.333
Strange?

00:09:15.333 --> 00:09:17.000
There's no cursor.

00:09:20.708 --> 00:09:22.708
Some kind of bug?

00:09:22.708 --> 00:09:24.458
Probably.

00:09:24.458 --> 00:09:29.042
Why is a little kid
like this playing SAO?

00:09:31.792 --> 00:09:34.458
At any rate, we can't leave her.

00:09:34.458 --> 00:09:38.833
We can figure things out once
she wakes up. Let's take her home.

00:09:39.333 --> 00:09:40.625
Yeah.

00:09:46.500 --> 00:09:48.708
One thing's for sure.

00:09:48.708 --> 00:09:53.000
Since we were able to move
her here, she can't be an NPC.

00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:55.167
That's true...

00:09:55.542 --> 00:10:01.083
Picking up an NPC would have
given you a harassment warning.

00:10:01.583 --> 00:10:05.375
And she isn't a quest giver either.

00:10:05.667 --> 00:10:09.667
If she were, our quest log
would have been updated.

00:10:10.625 --> 00:10:13.958
Which means she's a player after all,

00:10:13.958 --> 00:10:18.333
one who lost her way back there.
That's the most likely scenario.

00:10:19.125 --> 00:10:22.333
But what was she doing out there?

00:10:22.708 --> 00:10:27.458
I don't know what her situation is,
but maybe she has parents or guardians?

00:10:27.458 --> 00:10:31.583
Yeah, she must've logged
in with her family, right?

00:10:31.583 --> 00:10:33.833
I hope they're safe.

00:10:34.417 --> 00:10:37.417
Hey, she'll wake up, right?

00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:41.167
Yeah, if her body hasn't disappeared,

00:10:41.167 --> 00:10:44.750
signals are traveling to
and from her NerveGear.

00:10:44.750 --> 00:10:47.667
I think she's in a sleeplike state.

00:10:47.667 --> 00:10:51.583
So I'm sure she'll wake up eventually.

00:10:53.708 --> 00:10:54.917
Yeah.

00:11:00.708 --> 00:11:02.750
Hey, Kirito?

00:11:07.292 --> 00:11:08.917
Honestly.

00:11:20.542 --> 00:11:21.750
<i>If...</i>

00:11:22.042 --> 00:11:25.625
<i>If she entered SAO all alone...</i>

00:11:26.458 --> 00:11:30.000
<i>If she's been alone in</i>
<i>this world for so long...</i>

00:11:37.167 --> 00:11:38.583
Good night.

00:11:38.583 --> 00:11:41.458
I hope you wake up tomorrow.

00:11:57.625 --> 00:12:00.417
K-Kirito! Wake up, Kirito!

00:12:02.500 --> 00:12:04.417
Morning... What's wrong?

00:12:04.417 --> 00:12:06.750
Hurry! Get over here!

00:12:10.875 --> 00:12:15.875
Thank goodness you woke up.
Do you remember what happened?

00:12:20.625 --> 00:12:22.250
I see...

00:12:22.250 --> 00:12:25.083
What's your name?
Can you tell me?

00:12:25.500 --> 00:12:28.333
N-Name...

00:12:28.875 --> 00:12:32.208
My name...

00:12:33.333 --> 00:12:34.792
Yui?

00:12:35.042 --> 00:12:38.083
Yui... That's my name.

00:12:38.708 --> 00:12:41.833
Yui, huh? That's a nice name.

00:12:41.833 --> 00:12:45.250
I'm Asuna. This is Kirito.

00:12:45.917 --> 00:12:47.542
Auna?

00:12:47.875 --> 00:12:49.542
Kito?

00:12:50.333 --> 00:12:54.125
Hey, Yui, what were
you doing in the forest?

00:12:54.125 --> 00:12:57.458
Are your mom and dad somewhere?

00:12:59.542 --> 00:13:01.542
I don't know...

00:13:02.083 --> 00:13:05.167
I don't know anything.

00:13:05.667 --> 00:13:07.625
That's awful.

00:13:09.583 --> 00:13:11.333
Hello, Yui.

00:13:13.333 --> 00:13:15.375
Can I call you Yui?

00:13:16.542 --> 00:13:21.250
Okay. Then I want
you to call me Kirito.

00:13:21.833 --> 00:13:23.750
Kito?

00:13:23.750 --> 00:13:26.792
It's Kirito. Ki-ri-to.

00:13:29.583 --> 00:13:30.958
Kito.

00:13:31.792 --> 00:13:36.958
Maybe it's a little hard. You can
call me whatever's easiest for you.

00:13:39.708 --> 00:13:41.167
Daddy.

00:13:41.167 --> 00:13:42.417
Me?

00:13:44.042 --> 00:13:46.917
Auna is Mommy.

00:13:53.500 --> 00:13:56.792
That's right. I'm your mommy, Yui!

00:13:58.208 --> 00:13:59.667
Mommy!

00:13:59.958 --> 00:14:02.083
Daddy! Mommy!

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:05.708
You must be hungry! Let's eat.

00:14:05.708 --> 00:14:06.958
Yeah!

00:14:12.208 --> 00:14:15.208
Here you go. This one's yours, Yui.

00:14:21.958 --> 00:14:25.042
Yui, this is super spicy.

00:14:28.125 --> 00:14:30.875
I want the same one as Daddy.

00:14:30.875 --> 00:14:34.833
I see. If you think
you're ready, I won't stop you.

00:14:34.833 --> 00:14:37.792
Everything in life
is an experience!

00:14:51.125 --> 00:14:52.542
It's good...

00:14:52.542 --> 00:14:57.875
She's got guts. Tonight, we'll do
a full extra-spicy challenge course.

00:14:59.208 --> 00:15:03.375
Jeez, don't get carried away!
I'm not cooking that!

00:15:03.375 --> 00:15:06.208
--You heard her.
--You heard her?

00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:19.458
What do you think, Kirito?

00:15:20.375 --> 00:15:23.292
She doesn't seem
to have any memories.

00:15:23.292 --> 00:15:26.417
But more importantly,
from the look of things...

00:15:26.417 --> 00:15:29.417
It's like she's regressed into a baby.

00:15:29.417 --> 00:15:31.792
I... I...

00:15:33.750 --> 00:15:37.125
I'm sorry. I don't know what to do...

00:15:38.083 --> 00:15:43.542
You want to take care of her
until she regains her memory, right?

00:15:44.000 --> 00:15:45.708
Yeah, but...

00:15:46.125 --> 00:15:48.083
It's a dilemma.

00:15:48.083 --> 00:15:53.333
If we don't get back to the front lines,
it'll be that much longer till she's freed.

00:15:53.333 --> 00:15:54.542
Yeah.

00:15:55.875 --> 00:15:58.917
Let's do what we can for now.

00:15:58.917 --> 00:16:03.750
Given her gear, I can't imagine
she's been out in the field every day.

00:16:04.583 --> 00:16:09.375
Let's check the Town of Beginnings
first for any of her family members.

00:16:09.750 --> 00:16:11.000
Right.

00:16:11.250 --> 00:16:14.750
I don't want to say
goodbye to her, either.

00:16:15.667 --> 00:16:16.833
Kirito?

00:16:17.417 --> 00:16:21.583
I don't know how to express it.
It hasn't been long.

00:16:21.583 --> 00:16:26.083
But having her here has
made this feel like a real home.

00:16:26.083 --> 00:16:28.292
It just feels that way.

00:16:28.917 --> 00:16:30.375
Yeah.

00:16:30.375 --> 00:16:36.125
But it's not like we'll never see her again.
And if she has a family or guardian,

00:16:36.125 --> 00:16:38.958
they're probably worried right now.

00:16:38.958 --> 00:16:43.083
Yeah. When she wakes up,
we'll go to the Town of Beginnings.

00:16:43.458 --> 00:16:48.958
Make sure you can pull your weapons
out quickly. That place is Army territory.

00:16:49.750 --> 00:16:52.208
We should keep our guard up.

00:16:52.208 --> 00:16:53.417
Mommy...

00:16:53.958 --> 00:16:55.250
Daddy.

00:16:59.375 --> 00:17:02.250
"October 31, 2024"       "Floor 1: Town of Beginnings"

00:17:02.250 --> 00:17:04.792
I haven't been here in ages.

00:17:04.792 --> 00:17:06.292
Me neither.

00:17:13.542 --> 00:17:17.375
Yui, do you remember
any of these buildings?

00:17:19.542 --> 00:17:21.167
I don't know.

00:17:22.042 --> 00:17:25.583
Well, the Town of
Beginnings is really big.

00:17:25.958 --> 00:17:28.667
Let's start at the central market.

00:17:30.792 --> 00:17:32.542
Hey, Kirito...

00:17:33.583 --> 00:17:37.000
How many players are here currently?

00:17:37.500 --> 00:17:39.625
Hmm, let's see...

00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:43.750
About 6,000 players
are still alive in SAO.

00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:48.750
Around 30 percent are in the Town
of Beginnings, including the Army...

00:17:48.750 --> 00:17:50.875
Maybe less than 2,000?

00:17:50.875 --> 00:17:53.958
Then isn't the place a little empty?

00:17:53.958 --> 00:17:55.625
You're right.

00:17:57.667 --> 00:17:59.458
Give back the children!

00:17:59.833 --> 00:18:02.292
Hey, it's the day-care lady.

00:18:02.292 --> 00:18:04.875
We've been waiting for you!

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:06.833
Return the children!

00:18:07.708 --> 00:18:10.833
You make it sound like
we're doing something bad.

00:18:11.042 --> 00:18:15.542
We're just teaching them
how things work around here.

00:18:15.750 --> 00:18:18.750
This is also one of
the Army's key duties.

00:18:18.750 --> 00:18:22.958
That's right. Because
citizens have a duty to pay taxes.

00:18:25.375 --> 00:18:28.458
Ginn! Cain! Mina!
Are you over there?

00:18:30.458 --> 00:18:31.833
Miss Sasha!

00:18:31.833 --> 00:18:33.583
Save us!

00:18:33.792 --> 00:18:37.375
Forget the money.
Just give it all to them!

00:18:37.375 --> 00:18:40.208
That's not good enough!

00:18:41.333 --> 00:18:45.125
You guys owe a hell
of a lot of back taxes.

00:18:45.125 --> 00:18:49.625
So you need to leave your
equipment, along with all your armor.

00:18:49.750 --> 00:18:51.750
Every last piece.

00:18:53.667 --> 00:18:54.875
Get...

00:18:54.875 --> 00:18:56.917
Get out of the way!

00:18:56.917 --> 00:18:58.375
Or else...

00:19:07.625 --> 00:19:10.500
It's okay.
Put your equipment back on.

00:19:10.500 --> 00:19:12.125
R-Right.

00:19:13.458 --> 00:19:17.417
Hey. What's this?
Who the hell are you guys?

00:19:18.083 --> 00:19:21.208
You mean to interfere
with our mission?

00:19:21.208 --> 00:19:23.167
Well, hold on.

00:19:23.833 --> 00:19:26.625
I haven't seen you around before...

00:19:26.625 --> 00:19:30.917
You know what it means to defy
the Liberation Army, don't you?

00:19:33.708 --> 00:19:36.458
Kirito, take care of Yui.

00:19:36.458 --> 00:19:37.458
Right.

00:20:00.792 --> 00:20:02.333
Don't worry.

00:20:02.333 --> 00:20:06.167
In a safe zone, your HP
won't take a hit, no matter what.

00:20:06.583 --> 00:20:10.583
That's right. There's just
a mild knock-back effect.

00:20:10.583 --> 00:20:14.958
But on the other hand, safe-zone fights
leave you with a sense of terror.

00:20:16.417 --> 00:20:17.833
Don't!

00:20:21.333 --> 00:20:24.625
D-Don't just stand there!
Do something!

00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:51.583
Wow.

00:20:52.042 --> 00:20:54.542
That was amazing, big sister!

00:20:54.792 --> 00:20:59.208
--I've never seen anything like that!
--Yeah, you were so cool!

00:20:59.208 --> 00:21:01.500
--Thank you.
--Thanks!

00:21:04.083 --> 00:21:05.542
I wanna try too!

00:21:05.542 --> 00:21:09.167
See? Your mom's
crazy strong, isn't she?

00:21:13.333 --> 00:21:14.750
Everyone's...

00:21:16.125 --> 00:21:18.375
Everyone's hearts...

00:21:19.167 --> 00:21:20.250
Yui?

00:21:20.875 --> 00:21:21.917
Yui?

00:21:22.792 --> 00:21:25.375
--Yui, what's wrong?
--Everyone's hearts...

00:21:25.375 --> 00:21:26.417
Yui?

00:21:26.750 --> 00:21:29.625
Yui, did you remember something?

00:21:30.000 --> 00:21:32.833
I... I...

00:21:33.333 --> 00:21:36.417
I wasn't here...

00:21:37.458 --> 00:21:41.000
I was always alone in the dark...

00:21:53.167 --> 00:21:54.792
--Yui!
--Yui!

00:21:57.333 --> 00:21:59.792
Mommy, I'm scared...

00:21:59.792 --> 00:22:01.042
Mommy...

00:22:02.417 --> 00:22:05.208
What was that, just now?

00:22:11.292 --> 00:22:12.708
Yui.

00:22:30.042 --> 00:22:41.542
<i>The tolling of the faraway bells</i>
<i>sounded a little lonely to me</i>

00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:53.375
<i>So I tried harder, one more time,</i>
<i>this time soaring higher, all the way up</i>

00:22:53.750 --> 00:22:59.292
<i>Neither this reality that just keeps repeating itself</i>

00:22:59.625 --> 00:23:05.125
<i>Nor all my wishes, as numerous as the stars</i>

00:23:05.542 --> 00:23:10.542
<i>Now that I've found the tomorrow</i>
<i>I should strive for</i>

00:23:10.875 --> 00:23:15.833
<i>None of them can overcome these feelings of mine</i>

00:23:16.167 --> 00:23:22.667
<i>A world without end, opening up before my eyes</i>

00:23:23.000 --> 00:23:26.625
<i>Even if it's no more than a dream</i>

00:23:27.167 --> 00:23:33.875
<i>Even if I'm still lost, deep in my heart, it is strong</i>

00:23:34.208 --> 00:23:39.667
<i>Echoing forever and ever</i>

00:23:40.000 --> 00:23:46.208
<i>Shining softly, ever so softly</i>

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:53.110
Next Time: "Yui's Heart."
